ers with undiminished power and persuasiveness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Shakespeare.2bisacsh1 aHerder, Johann Gottfried, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Gregory, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Gregory, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044250240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140082825840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400828258423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400828258.jpg  a978-3-11-044250-2  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK